parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not lock up, leading to increased risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt warning light and buzzer activate
the seat belt tightens up unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can cause the seat belt to not release or lock up, leading to increased risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt will not release

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to come undone, leading to increased risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
The failure of the frontal crash restraints can cause the seat belt to not hold the passenger in place, leading to increased risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt does not hold the passenger in place
the seat belt fails to restrain during a frontal crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of fuel system hoses can lead to liquid fuel leakage, increasing the risk of fire hazards, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
The failure of fuel injectors can cause engine hesitation, transmission hesitation, and decreased vehicle performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the fuel pump can cause engine hesitation, transmission hesitation, and decreased vehicle performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure (Slipping, Hanging, or Not Shifting Properly)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in a particular gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: transmission hangs up in a particular gear
transmission does not shift properly into gear
transmission remains in neutral after shifting to drive gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.
